comments.text:
People say that those who drink Starbucks are pretentious? Try the people 
who don't drink Starbucks. The gagging in the beginning of the video was so 
unnecessary and disgusting. It's just coffee. The best tea I've had is 
worse than the worst coffee I've had. And I've only recently started 
drinking straight up coffee. The best drink is probably the vanilla latte, 
though. The white chocolate latte is really good, but it's too sweet and 
rich, so even a tall is too much. My go-to drink on a hot day is a venti 
iced coffee with hazelnut, and then on a cold day it's a grande hot coffee 
with vanilla. Both under $3 and so delicious. Also Pike Place is definitely 
the best brew they have. It's the medium roast. Still strong enough to get 
me awake in the morning.﻿

Pro tip for all you frap lovers out there. Go to starbucks and ask for a 
"Surprise venti frappachino." It gives them a chance to have fun/experiment 
with the drink, you will more than likely get a drink that's not on the 
menu (I've gotten butterfingers and reeses flavors before), and it gives 
you a chance to make conversation with the baristas. I don't even have to 
order anymore, they just make one, and I'm also known as the "Frappachino 
guy."

Don't do this if it's crowded though, then you're just an ass.﻿
